Gulf Stocks: Arab National Bank of Saudi Arabia, Shuaa Capital

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-04-11T12:16:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/gulf-stocks-arab-national-bank-of-saudi-arabia-shuaa-capital.html
Dubai’s benchmark  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
gained to the highest in almost two months, advancing 0.2
percent to 1,572.98 at the 2:00 p.m. close in the emirate. Abu
Dhabi’s gauge rose 0.4 percent and Qatar’s benchmark index
increased 1 percent. Saudi Arabia’s Tadawul All Share Index
added 0.1 percent at 2:38 p.m. in Riyadh.  The following shares rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.  Arab National Bank (ARNB)   slid the most in two weeks,
dropping 2 percent to 34.2 Saudi riyals. Saudi Arabia’s sixth-
largest publicly traded lender by assets said first-quarter
profit declined to 587 million riyals ($156.5 million) from 634
million riyals a year earlier as operating expenses increased.  Shuaa Capital PSC (SHUAA)   jumped 4.4 percent to 1.18
dirhams, the highest level since Feb. 15. The United Arab
Emirates’ biggest investment bank said the Tunisian Financial
Market Council lifted the freeze on its brokerage accounts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
 asalha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
